Former Colombia goalkeeper Calero dies at 41
MEXICO CITY (Reuters) - Former Colombia goalkeeper Miguel Calero died at the age of 41 on Tuesday, one week after being taken to hospital suffering from cerebral thrombosis, his ex-club Pachuca said in a statement.
Calero won 51 caps for his country, taking part in the Copa America six times, and was in the squad at the 1992 Olympic Games and 1998 World Cup.